story.title: Spiderlings - Episode 5
story.storyDescription: Danny shouldn’t have popped the bump on his cheek! Baby spiders were inside, and now they’re taking control.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: V. Gardner has a black thumb, bringing death and destruction to every plant she tries to grow. To make up for it, she painted her office forest green and pretends she’s in the darkest corner of the woods as she writes.

story.prePaywallNotification: Does Mama Spider want Danny to LIVE or DIE? Read SPIDERLINGS.
story.postPaywallNotification: Will Bryan try to save Danny from the swarm of deadly bugs? Keep reading SPIDERLINGS.

messages.text: She needs you to stay alive.
She knows that’s the only way she can protect her young.
Without you, she’s vulnerable. She’s weak.
She knows that if you die, we’ll quickly eliminate her and the rest of the cluster.
Not comforting.
She shifted. I can breathe.
Were you…were you TELLING her to keep me alive there?
I told you, I have a plan.
She has a human mother’s need to protect.
A shewolf’s hunger.
A lioness’s ferocity.
A queen bee’s control.
A black widow’s cunning.
My career achievement.
For fuck’s sake, Mom.
This is a hell of a way to smash the patriarchy.
We were so careful — only one percent of the mutated spiders were capable of breeding.
But that one percent surpassed our greatest expectations.
We had to stop the program.
I’m so thirsty.
Maybe you could sip some water.
I’m not thirsty for water.
What is happening to me?
Don’t worry about that now.
I have a plan, Danny.
Does it involve Bryan?
NO! I told you, don’t answer his texts.
He sent me one just now.
Says he’s on the way to our house.
To check on me,
DO NOT LET HIM IN.
Susan texts Bryan.
Stay away from my son!
Danny?
I just want to check on the poor, sick kid.
Being a good coworker and all.
Enough already, Bryan.
You’ve done enough!
Should I stop for some chicken soup?
Or is he slurping up something else these days?
I knew you were sick. Knew you were corrupt.
You’d do anything to get ahead.
That’s what sets the winners apart from the losers.
You’re so stupid, Bryan!
I told Corporate that you were unstable.
Told them I thought you could be compromised.
And here you go, proving my case.
You bitch.
You think you’re so smart — that maternal instincts trump brute strength.
Your instincts were a bit off here, huh?
Your best shot is to run, Bryan.
Leave Corporate. Leave the country.
LEAVE MY SON ALONE.
There’s another thing you don’t know.
After Project Arachnid is destroyed, Corporate is going to announce my promotion.
Needless to say, you’ll be fired.
Nah. I’m going to stick around.
Corporate will see that I’m the one for the job when I stop the spider apocalypse.
So that’s what this is about?
So you can pull some Save the Day scheme?
With my son caught in the middle?
Sacrifices must be made.
Isn’t that what you always say?
How’s little Danny doing?
Danny is strong.
He’s going to be fine.
I’m going to save him.
I’m the only one who can do that.
I’m your white knight, sweetheart.
Remember our little failsafe?
The “natural defense” YOU insisted we program into the spiderlings?
Why do you think I’m not home right now, Bryan?
I’m looking for the code.
Once I unlock the vault, I’ll stop this horrible mess you’ve created.
Mess? I see it more as a tangled web.
You’re sick.
And you’re still in the parking lot at the lab.
You have to stay close enough to hack into the wifi, I assume.
Are you tracking me?
I guess we all have our little secrets.
It doesn’t matter.
Once I have the cure, all I need to do is get close enough to Mama.
And then all of this will be over.
You’re never going to find the code.
Because I erased it this morning.
HOW COULD YOU?
I guess you need me after all.
I’ll figure out another way.
Have they molted a second time?
It won’t be long before they need to feed again.
Until they turn on Danny.
Mama won’t turn on Danny.
That’s the theory.
But the experiment never got to play out, did it?
Back off, Bryan.
You’re dangerous.
You’ve already put my family in enough jeopardy.
Just go.
And let you get all the glory?
I don’t think so.
Of course, now that I think about it, this won’t work out so well for you.
After all, you were careless enough to bring home a mama spider — an assassin — on your sneaker.
Like I said, for all your ramblings about maternal instincts…
They sure haven’t helped you, huh?
Corporate will see that YOU did this, Bryan.
I don’t think so.
I think the best-case scenario is that you rot in jail.
Worst case, your family is destroyed.
Sacrifices must be made.
I’m going to tell you one more time:
STAY AWAY FROM MY SON
Mom?
Mom I need you.
I’m right here, Danny.
I have a plan.
It’s too late! Something’s happening!
They all scattered.
My heart is hammering so fast. Can’t breathe!
Try to stay calm.
Choking
momomomom
The doorbell rings.
